It was my job.

00:30:15.420 --> 00:30:21.420
I didn't find any glory or thinking that I was exceptional.

00:30:21.420 --> 00:30:25.420
I just was trained to do the job and did it.

00:30:28.420 --> 00:30:31.420
And as I said, I would do the whole thing again.

00:30:31.420 --> 00:30:40.420
The amount of training must have been extensive for your survival, your navigation, everything.

00:30:40.420 --> 00:30:47.420
Yes, and seven miles a minute you could get lost very quickly.

00:30:47.420 --> 00:30:53.420
But I mean even your ground stuff, in the case of being shot down or...

00:30:53.420 --> 00:30:55.420
Oh, survival, absolutely, yes.

00:30:55.420 --> 00:30:57.420
You survived on techniques.

00:30:57.420 --> 00:30:59.420
I mean, the joke about the winter survival one.

00:30:59.420 --> 00:31:05.420
The one thing that I took from that course was if you ended up in snow, deep snow,

00:31:05.420 --> 00:31:12.420
and you could see a house or something where you might think you could find safety,

00:31:12.420 --> 00:31:24.420
you made sure that you were going to get there because you just might only get halfway and then die with cold or whatever.

00:31:24.420 --> 00:31:30.420
You had to be certain before you left where you were because all your kit was with you.

00:31:33.420 --> 00:31:34.420
Interesting.

00:31:36.420 --> 00:31:37.420
Good fun.

00:31:37.420 --> 00:31:40.420
And then the next one was down at Bad Kohlbrück in Germany,

00:31:40.420 --> 00:31:46.420
which is another minus 18, we are feet sticking out of a parachute tent.

00:31:46.420 --> 00:31:48.420
That was cold that.

00:31:48.420 --> 00:31:53.420
And when the morning came, you thought, oh, bloody hell, I know not to...

00:31:53.420 --> 00:31:54.420
Yes.

00:31:54.420 --> 00:31:55.420
...end up in the snow.

00:31:55.420 --> 00:31:59.420
No, yeah, you know, if it happens, you had an idea what to do then.

00:32:00.420 --> 00:32:03.420
What was the kit that you were given?

00:32:03.420 --> 00:32:05.420
Like, was it good enough for those sort of conditions?

00:32:05.420 --> 00:32:07.420
Oh, the survival kit, yeah.

00:32:07.420 --> 00:32:08.420
Oh, that's really good.

00:32:08.420 --> 00:32:11.420
Maybe the part of the ejection seat had a whole box full of stuff.

00:32:14.420 --> 00:32:17.420
Dare I say, I've still got the machete.

00:32:20.420 --> 00:32:21.420
But good fun, good fun.

00:32:21.420 --> 00:32:22.420
Yeah, it's good fun.

00:32:24.420 --> 00:32:25.420
Yeah, good fun.

00:32:26.420 --> 00:32:27.420
Do it all again.

00:32:28.420 --> 00:32:31.420
Have to try and find a way of finding that crash site.

00:32:33.420 --> 00:32:36.420
They are on to it and I'm told that they're going to find it.

00:32:36.420 --> 00:32:39.420
Well, Coombe Ristwith was the village that I was told.

00:32:39.420 --> 00:32:40.420
Yes.

00:32:41.420 --> 00:32:42.420
But that's in a...

00:32:43.420 --> 00:32:45.420
Do you know, recently I've been there, Coombe Ristwith.

00:32:45.420 --> 00:32:46.420
I couldn't believe it.

00:32:47.420 --> 00:32:48.420
I've been here before.

00:32:48.420 --> 00:32:51.420
But that was when the four of us came up to try and find the crash site.

00:32:51.420 --> 00:32:55.420
And how many years ago? Was it 20 years ago you said that you went to find that?

00:32:55.420 --> 00:32:58.420
Oh, no, that was more recent, maybe 10 years ago.

00:32:58.420 --> 00:32:59.420
10 years ago.

00:33:01.420 --> 00:33:05.420
1982, just before the Falkens War, was the crash.

00:33:07.420 --> 00:33:09.420
Coombe Ristwith on the hill behind...

00:33:10.420 --> 00:33:11.420
The southern hill.

00:33:11.420 --> 00:33:14.420
And there was a valley, I can still remember the valley.

00:33:15.420 --> 00:33:17.420
And there was nothing else there.

00:33:19.420 --> 00:33:20.420
Except the old sheep.

00:33:21.420 --> 00:33:22.420
Didn't they...

00:33:23.420 --> 00:33:26.420
The crash collision went there, didn't they?

00:33:26.420 --> 00:33:28.420
And they would have recovered everything.

00:33:28.420 --> 00:33:29.420
Absolutely.

00:33:30.420 --> 00:33:36.420
But, you know, just a wonderful experience because I've kept in touch with these guys that came up with me, which was nice.

00:33:38.420 --> 00:33:40.420
Ex-Navy Air Force.

00:33:41.420 --> 00:33:43.420
And Marines.

00:33:44.420 --> 00:33:46.420
And we got on well, surprisingly.

